ohai .vim

1_ install macvim if you're on, um, a mac (needed to get vim with +ruby)
$ brew install macvim --override-system-vim

1_a_ also install cmake for YouCompleteMe
$ brew install cmake

2_ clone this bad boy into ~/.vim
$ git clone https://github.com/bergren2/dotvim.git ~/.vim

3_ install stuff -- .vimrc, .gvimrc, .ackrc
$ ruby ~/.vim/install.rb

4_ install vundle
$ git clone https://github.com/gmarik/vundle.git ~/.vim/bundle/vundle

5_ bundle install! lolol
$ vim +BundleInstall +qall

6_ YOU COMPLETE ME
$ cd ~/.vim/bundle/YouCompleteMe
$ ./install.sh --clang-completer

one day i'll vim stuff on linux and i'll update this then
